<dec f='include/sys/io.h' l='32' type='int ioperm(unsigned long __from, unsigned long __num, int __turn_on)'/>
<doc f='include/sys/io.h' l='25'>/* If TURN_ON is TRUE, request for permission to do direct i/o on the
   port numbers in the range [FROM,FROM+NUM-1].  Otherwise, turn I/O
   permission off for that range.  This call requires root privileges.

   Portability note: not all Linux platforms support this call.  Most
   platforms based on the PC I/O architecture probably will, however.
   E.g., Linux/Alpha for Alpha PCs supports this.  */</doc>
